    "description": "SIIX Corporation primarily sells and distributes electronic components in Japan, China, the rest of Asia, Europe, and the Americas. The company offers automotive electronic components, such as automotive exteriors, meters, ECU, switches, quasi-millimeter wave radars, ABS, cameras, battery sensors, car multimedia, etc., as well as industrial equipment, such as engine ignition devices for power tools, battery packs, aircraft-borne electronic devices, inverters, medical devices, smart meters, industrial sewing machines, etc. It also provides home appliances, such as digital appliances, air conditioners, refrigerators, educational toys, healthcare equipment, electronic musical instruments, etc.; information devices, including office equipment, OA equipment, projectors, etc.; and automobile wire harness, motorcycles, inks, and other electronic components, etc. In addition, the company is involved in plastic molding and die manufacturing, and circuit board mounting, as well as provision of materials procurement, assembly, and processing of devices and components; and logistics services. SIIX Corporation was founded in 1957 and is headquartered in Osaka, Japan."
